136
00:06:32,905 --> 00:06:37,132
<i>we used to be friends a long time ago</i>

137
00:06:37,437 --> 00:06:39,521
<i>we used to be friends</i>

138
00:06:45,281 --> 00:06:48,940
Amelia signed the settlement 
papers with Kane Software...

139
00:06:49,227 --> 00:06:51,065
last spring.

140
00:06:53,201 --> 00:06:56,632
And what was the going rate 
for taking the fall for murder?

141
00:06:57,603 --> 00:06:59,309
$3 million.

142
00:06:59,652 --> 00:07:01,801
It was for Amelia.

143
00:07:02,049 --> 00:07:04,803
You don't think making herself 
scarce was part of the settlement?

144
00:07:04,995 --> 00:07:06,758
I need you to find her.

145
00:07:09,012 --> 00:07:10,514
Why should I help you?

146
00:07:10,640 --> 00:07:12,112
Because I'm begging you.

147
00:07:15,205 --> 00:07:20,755
I missed her 21st birthday, 
and I won't live to see her 22nd.

148
00:07:23,125 --> 00:07:25,325
Please? What are you doing?

149
00:07:26,217 --> 00:07:29,150
Broke or not, there has to be 
a hospital that'll take you.

150
00:07:29,684 --> 00:07:31,674
Hi. I need to bring someone in.

151
00:07:31,885 --> 00:07:32,954
Where is your E.R. entrance?
-- Forget about me.

152
00:07:32,965 --> 00:07:35,241
Will you help me find my daughter?

153
00:07:35,333 --> 00:07:36,130
Thank you.

154
00:07:37,916 --> 00:07:39,888
Only because you begged.

155
00:07:40,515 --> 00:07:41,368
Come on.

156
00:07:41,369 --> 00:07:42,494
Number four, step forward.

157
00:07:43,198 --> 00:07:45,969
Oh, wow, I'm stunned.

158
00:07:46,709 --> 00:07:47,733
You like me.

159
00:07:48,321 --> 00:07:49,794
You really like me.

160
00:07:50,571 --> 00:07:54,496
Well, first I'd just like 
to say the other, uh, nominees

161
00:07:54,989 --> 00:07:57,871
are all such wonderfully gifted criminals.

162
00:07:58,213 --> 00:07:59,749
And I want to thank my agent...

163
00:08:01,021 --> 00:08:02,103
...and my publicist

164
00:08:02,824 --> 00:08:04,246
for always shooting me from the left side.

165
00:08:06,305 --> 00:08:07,165
You might want to get a lawyer.

166
00:08:07,734 --> 00:08:08,909
What? For this charade?

167
00:08:11,193 --> 00:08:14,346
Just get me the first sober
public defender you find in the hall,

168
00:08:14,739 --> 00:08:17,148
put the bail on my black amex, 
and call me a limo.

169
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:19,967
Actually, buddy...

170
00:08:20,404 --> 00:08:22,186
it's kind of hard to get bail 
without a hearing.

171
00:08:22,548 --> 00:08:24,140
And even if you make it before a judge,

172
00:08:24,595 --> 00:08:26,207
I draw a lot of water in town,

173
00:08:26,674 --> 00:08:30,162
and I got this feeling you might 
just get declared a flight risk.

174
00:08:30,713 --> 00:08:31,604
Hmm?

175
00:08:32,741 --> 00:08:36,631
Amelia held up her end of the deal with 
Jake Kane and vanished completely.

176
00:08:37,123 --> 00:08:39,305
Her paper trail dried up on may 27th.

177
00:08:39,628 --> 00:08:43,085
But it's been my experience 
that personal ties don't dry up so easily,

178
00:08:43,730 --> 00:08:47,454
and last I saw her, she was tied pretty 
tightly to a certain boyfriend.

179
00:08:54,875 --> 00:08:56,620
Hi. Are you mike?

180
00:08:57,231 --> 00:08:58,371
I don't know where she is.

181
00:08:58,694 --> 00:09:00,855
The last place I saw her was in Ibiza.

182
00:09:01,463 --> 00:09:04,932
You mean like "there's Tara Reid 
passed out on the beach" Ibiza?

183
00:09:05,123 --> 00:09:07,835
Yeah. I'd just finished finals, 
and she came up and said,

184
00:09:07,836 --> 00:09:09,436
"hey, I got a whole bunch of money."

185
00:09:09,798 --> 00:09:11,087
Oh, a patent settlement.

186
00:09:11,354 --> 00:09:12,922
It was complicated.

187
00:09:13,490 --> 00:09:14,724
Well, we went to Europe,

188
00:09:14,972 --> 00:09:16,644
ended up in Ibiza.

189
00:09:16,812 --> 00:09:19,352
We met fun people. We went 
to the beach every single day,

190
00:09:19,488 --> 00:09:22,194
tracked down all these cool 
parties on this website.

191
00:09:22,368 --> 00:09:22,842
It was cool.

192
00:09:23,486 --> 00:09:24,644
I'm sensing an "until."

193
00:09:25,131 --> 00:09:28,335
One night we're at this club 
one of these places

194
00:09:28,452 --> 00:09:30,475
that drop this foam crap on you at midnight.

195
00:09:30,931 --> 00:09:32,519
So, we're there.

196
00:09:32,917 --> 00:09:33,506
We're hanging out.

197
00:09:33,811 --> 00:09:34,967
They drop the foam...

198
00:09:36,583 --> 00:09:38,857
and that was the last I saw of her.

199
00:09:39,280 --> 00:09:40,249
Did you check under the foam?

200
00:09:40,949 --> 00:09:42,727
I had to call my parents to fly me home.

201
00:09:43,313 --> 00:09:44,811
It basically kind of sucked.

202
00:09:45,138 --> 00:09:47,038
Well, at least you got to go to Europe.

203
00:09:47,343 --> 00:09:49,047
And all I got was this lousy t-shirt.

204
00:09:49,333 --> 00:09:51,913
So you're not... worried?

205
00:09:52,143 --> 00:09:53,673
She ditched me. Whatever.

206
00:09:54,403 --> 00:09:56,645
The girl's got three million bucks 
to keep her company.

207
00:09:56,780 --> 00:09:58,715
If she's really in trouble, 
she took all my phone cards.

208
00:09:58,833 --> 00:10:02,852
She could call me, but... 
I kind of doubt that's gonna happen.

209
00:10:03,307 --> 00:10:05,942
Okay, boyfriend ditched in Ibiza.

210
00:10:06,722 --> 00:10:09,336
Maybe Amelia's old roommate 
got the behind-the-scenes on that.

211
00:10:09,962 --> 00:10:11,784
God. She really went to Ibiza?

212
00:10:12,107 --> 00:10:13,263
Or maybe not.

213
00:10:13,701 --> 00:10:16,924
Did she contact you? Anything 
about where she might have been?

214
00:10:16,925 --> 00:10:19,028
No, she just, you know, left.

215
00:10:19,997 --> 00:10:23,183
Ibiza. That is so weird.

216
00:10:23,393 --> 00:10:24,665
Weird? How so?

217
00:10:24,989 --> 00:10:26,904
Well, she's hardly 
the "girls gone wild" type.

218
00:10:27,096 --> 00:10:29,163
I practically had to put a gun to her head

219
00:10:29,280 --> 00:10:31,707
just to get her to do the greek
booze cruise last year.

220
00:10:31,785 --> 00:10:33,399
