which means they have gps coordinates.

499
00:24:35,750 --> 00:24:37,727
Okay, thank you very much.

500
00:24:39,927 --> 00:24:42,898
Okay. So, two days ago, 
they were right here.

501
00:24:42,964 --> 00:24:44,548
Waverly, California?

502
00:24:44,652 --> 00:24:47,537
Thank you so much. 
Please call if you know anything else.

503
00:24:47,645 --> 00:24:49,045
I hope your boss gets canned.

504
00:24:50,810 --> 00:24:51,765
Yours, too.

505
00:24:57,287 --> 00:24:58,221
So, what'd you find?

506
00:24:58,312 --> 00:24:59,748
I'm sorry. What?

507
00:25:00,498 --> 00:25:01,710
You brought up the bus.

508
00:25:01,929 --> 00:25:04,986
I want to know if your forensic guys 
found any evidence of an explosion.

509
00:25:05,190 --> 00:25:08,352
Look, Keith, when you called 
on tuesday night to concede --

510
00:25:08,496 --> 00:25:10,260
I'm sorry I missed the call, by the way --

511
00:25:10,414 --> 00:25:13,399
I figured you were conceding 
your involvement in this case.

512
00:25:13,493 --> 00:25:16,144
If I didn't turn over that 
voice mail Veronica found,

513
00:25:16,227 --> 00:25:18,209
that bus would still be 
on the bottom of the sea.

514
00:25:18,497 --> 00:25:21,019
Keith, we're on it.

515
00:25:21,662 --> 00:25:23,531
Maybe you should worry
a little less about the bus

516
00:25:23,639 --> 00:25:24,883
and a little more about your daughter.

517
00:25:25,741 --> 00:25:27,162
What's that supposed to mean?

518
00:25:28,022 --> 00:25:30,845
She didn't tell you? 
And you two seemed so close.

519
00:25:30,896 --> 00:25:31,407
Tell me what?

520
00:25:32,962 --> 00:25:36,541
It was a couple weeks back.
We had Veronica down to the station.

521
00:25:36,732 --> 00:25:40,737
Right, something about... 
her name written on a guy's hand,

522
00:25:41,422 --> 00:25:42,833
a guy who washed up on the beach.

523
00:25:43,098 --> 00:25:45,741
Forget it. She said it was nothing, so...

524
00:25:48,551 --> 00:25:49,869
you know kids these days.

525
00:25:55,029 --> 00:25:57,524
Okay, so now I know two things --

526
00:25:57,739 --> 00:26:03,301
where Amelia was two days ago and why 
I've never heard of Waverly, California.

527
00:26:16,436 --> 00:26:18,411
Actually, there's no "o" in "naughty."

528
00:26:18,471 --> 00:26:20,870
It's "knotty," with a "k," like in pine.

529
00:26:21,111 --> 00:26:22,960
I-I-I-it'S...research.

530
00:26:24,712 --> 00:26:27,628
"Knotty school girls"?
What will they think of next?

531
00:26:27,885 --> 00:26:31,121
You want a room? It's 30 bucks a night.

532
00:26:31,285 --> 00:26:32,687
Actually, I'm looking for someone.

533
00:26:32,956 --> 00:26:35,650
Well, if it's me, congratulations.

534
00:26:35,845 --> 00:26:38,529
Otherwise, unless you 
get lucky at the gas 'n' sip,

535
00:26:38,601 --> 00:26:41,422
your options are pretty limited around here.

536
00:26:41,644 --> 00:26:45,209
It's a friend. She probably passed 
through here in the last couple days.

537
00:26:45,303 --> 00:26:46,504
Have you seen her?

538
00:26:46,657 --> 00:26:49,940
Yeah. Yeah, she got 
a room a couple of days ago.

539
00:26:50,025 --> 00:26:51,342
Can I see the room she stayed in?

540
00:26:52,743 --> 00:26:57,724
Like I said... room's $30 a night.

541
00:27:10,986 --> 00:27:14,589
You've got millions of dollars,
and you've been partying all across Europe.

542
00:27:15,244 --> 00:27:17,406
What brings you here?

543
00:27:31,816 --> 00:27:32,594
Hey, dad.

544
00:27:32,698 --> 00:27:33,379
Where are you?

545
00:27:33,499 --> 00:27:34,642
What? I'm --

546
00:27:34,833 --> 00:27:35,936
Where are you right now?

547
00:27:37,415 --> 00:27:42,168
I'm... shopping in a funny 
little art gallery downtown.

548
00:27:42,754 --> 00:27:43,292
Show me.

549
00:27:44,403 --> 00:27:45,836
Dad, I don't know how I'm supposed to --

550
00:27:45,957 --> 00:27:48,636
Take a picture, 
send it to me, then I'll relax.

551
00:27:48,756 --> 00:27:53,108
And when you come home, you can 
tell me about the dead guy on the beach.

552
00:27:55,428 --> 00:27:56,902
How could you keep this from me?

553
00:27:59,705 --> 00:28:00,937
I didn't want you to worry.

554
00:28:01,179 --> 00:28:04,060
About what? What did you find?

555
00:28:06,050 --> 00:28:07,832
The guy on the beach is David Moran,

556
00:28:08,128 --> 00:28:09,555
A.K.A. "Curly."

557
00:28:09,855 --> 00:28:12,440
He knew Aaron Echolls from way back.

558
00:28:13,235 --> 00:28:14,986
He knew how to make a bus crash.

559
00:28:15,291 --> 00:28:16,003
What do you mean?

560
00:28:16,172 --> 00:28:19,269
He was a stunt man on 
a movie called "The Long Haul."

561
00:28:19,531 --> 00:28:21,127
It was Aaron's first big hit.

562
00:28:22,489 --> 00:28:24,536
You really think --

563
00:28:24,630 --> 00:28:27,217
I don't know. I don't know.

564
00:28:28,282 --> 00:28:33,254
But if it's true, if... Aaron is 
really trying to take out a witness,

565
00:28:33,406 --> 00:28:35,546
then that means all those
kids died because of me.

566
00:28:37,811 --> 00:28:43,313
And trying to figure it out is the only 
thing keeping me from going insane crazy.

567
00:28:43,471 --> 00:28:46,108
Otherwise I'd just obsess
about it 24 hours a day.

568
00:28:46,211 --> 00:28:47,977
Yeah. Yeah, I know the feeling.

569
00:28:48,101 --> 00:28:49,760
It's called being a parent.

570
00:28:51,960 --> 00:28:54,175
You send me that picture, 
and we'll talk when you get home.

571
00:29:17,915 --> 00:29:20,379
Is this what they imagined 
when they invented all this technology?

572
00:29:20,665 --> 00:29:22,598
A digital leash for a nervous parent?

573
00:29:25,013 --> 00:29:26,357
And speaking of technology,

574
00:29:26,443 --> 00:29:29,261
my bluetooth connection
is detecting Amelia's palm pilot.

575
00:29:29,544 --> 00:29:32,033
"Maximum range, 30 feet."

576
00:29:37,422 --> 00:29:38,751
Sorry to interrupt the research.

577
00:29:38,947 --> 00:29:41,293
Is there anyone staying
in the room past mine?

578
00:29:41,370 --> 00:29:45,578
Rooms...are...$30.

579
00:30:05,575 --> 00:30:07,141
Can I see the room this side of mine?

580
00:30:56,776 --> 00:30:58,940
I thought I told you
to mind your own business.

581
00:31:03,486 --> 00:31:05,767
My father knows where 
I am and what I'm doing.

582
00:31:05,887 --> 00:31:07,301
He knows --I'm guessing that was her?

583
00:31:08,170 --> 00:31:08,968
Amelia?

584
00:31:09,082 --> 00:31:10,492
In the ice machine?

585
00:31:12,561 --> 00:31:13,303
Wait.

586
00:31:21,997 --> 00:31:24,235
I wasn't entirely up-front 
with you the other day.

587
00:31:25,305 --> 00:31:27,685
Amelia signed her papers 
and disappeared just like I said.

588
00:31:28,349 --> 00:31:30,470
I considered the matter settled until --

589
00:31:30,614 --> 00:31:32,752
Until she made a call from
the pay phone across the street.

590
00:31:32,852 --> 00:31:35,090
No, that was the second 
call to arrange for the pickup.

591
00:31:35,447 --> 00:31:39,440
The first call was to extort an additional
quarter million from Kane Software.

592
00:31:39,731 --> 00:31:43,366
She wanted more money? 
She got three million bucks six months ago.

593
00:31:43,451 --> 00:31:45,965
I gave her the money -- marked bills --

594
00:31:46,200 --> 00:31:50,493
under the condition that she disappear 
until the Kanes' legal issues were settled.

595
00:31:51,402 --> 00:31:53,454
But a week after she's 
supposed to be on the plane,

596
00:31:53,775 --> 00:31:55,872
marked bills started showing up here.

597
00:31:56,816 --> 00:32:00,860
So, you did find someone at 
the gas 'n' sip, and now you need a room?

598
00:32:01,808 --> 00:32:04,873
Was anyone else in here two nights ago? 
Did you see anyone with her?

599
00:32:04,984 --> 00:32:07,290
Why? Is he missing a friend, too?

600
00:32:07,467 --> 00:32:09,887
Answer the question, 
or I'll break all your fingers.

601
00:32:10,663 --> 00:32:12,889
J-just the guy she come in with.

602
00:32:13,575 --> 00:32:14,692
What? You didn't ask.

603
00:32:14,831 --> 00:32:16,460
What did he look like?

604
00:32:16,556 --> 00:32:19,828
Brown hair, medium size, t-shirt.

605
00:32:22,927 --> 00:32:23,735
Thank you.

606
00:32:25,181 --> 00:32:25,842
You're welcome.

607
00:32:26,081 --> 00:32:27,138
That description rings a bell?

608
00:32:27,965 --> 00:32:28,557
Yeah.

609
00:32:28,863 --> 00:32:30,502
I need you to take me to this person.

610
00:32:31,189 --> 00:32:32,327
What about --

611
00:32:32,472 --> 00:32:33,632
no, I'll deal with the cops.

612
00:32:33,737 --> 00:32:36,583
I need a better handle
on this before things go too public.

613
00:32:44,175 --> 00:32:45,202
Just two chairs?

614
00:32:47,567 --> 00:32:48,809
Where's my lawyer going to sit?

615
00:32:48,937 --> 00:32:50,474
Oh, it's an unofficial visit,

616
00:32:51,104 --> 00:32:53,876
just me and the guard 
who'll deny I was ever here.

617
00:32:53,931 --> 00:32:54,974
Ah.

618
00:32:56,787 --> 00:33:01,214
Well... in that case, I hope 
you won't mind carrying the conversation.

619
00:33:01,323 --> 00:33:02,356
Have it your way.

620
00:33:03,857 --> 00:33:06,180
You look good. What do you got going on?

621
00:33:06,380 --> 00:33:07,899
Some weights? A little cardio?

622
00:33:09,688 --> 00:33:10,699
Well, I got a lot of free time.

623
00:33:13,342 --> 00:33:14,766
I just got my psychology degree.

624
00:33:15,776 --> 00:33:17,591
And now I'm reading the russian masters --

625
00:33:18,085 --> 00:33:21,362
Tolstoy, Turgenev... you know.

626
00:33:21,633 --> 00:33:25,058
So, did you come out here 
to talk self-improvement?

627
00:33:25,941 --> 00:33:27,885
I'm here because of my daughter.

628
00:33:28,156 --> 00:33:30,610
Oh, now that's funny. So am I.

629
00:33:30,781 --> 00:33:34,017
So, did you come here 
today to thank me, Keith?

630
00:33:34,700 --> 00:33:36,044
You know, for your 15 minutes?

631
00:33:36,346 --> 00:33:39,954
'Cause if it wasn't for me, no one 
would have bought that hack book of yours.

632
00:33:45,365 --> 00:33:46,906
I guess you didn't come to thank me.

633
00:33:48,468 --> 00:33:51,614
Maybe -- maybe you just 
came here to gloat, hmm?

634
00:33:53,666 --> 00:33:57,035
No, that doesn't seem like you much, either.

635
00:34:00,139 --> 00:34:02,142
Why did you come here, Keith?

636
00:34:02,318 --> 00:34:07,545
Former employee of yours shows up dead, 
sabotaged school bus goes over a cliff,

637
00:34:07,644 --> 00:34:09,931
and I start to worry 
about Veronica's safety.

638
00:34:09,981 --> 00:34:11,332
Whoa, whoa, whoa. Wait a minute.

639
00:34:11,387 --> 00:34:13,231
You think I had something 
to do with the crash?

640
00:34:14,888 --> 00:34:17,474
Whoo. Whoo-hoo, you are priceless, Keith!

641
00:34:17,977 --> 00:34:21,710
You know, they give enough press, you'd 
find a way to put me on the grassy knoll.

642
00:34:22,191 --> 00:34:25,957
Truth is... I don't care 
if you're behind the crash or not.

643
00:34:26,065 --> 00:34:30,372
I just want you to know that if anything 
happens to my daughter in, say, the next...

644
00:34:30,829 --> 00:34:34,810
70, 80 years, you're the one 
who's going to pay for it.

645
00:34:36,867 --> 00:34:40,163
Now, did you come all the way out here
just to give me that tough-guy speech?

646
00:34:40,431 --> 00:34:43,869
No, I came all the way out here 
to show how easily I can get to you.

647
00:34:44,846 --> 00:34:48,775
So just... file that away.

648
00:35:02,489 --> 00:35:03,562
Hey, what's going on?

649
00:35:05,915 --> 00:35:08,733
What are you doing? You said 
you were going to ask him some questions.

650
00:35:11,174 --> 00:35:13,361
I'm going to ask you some 
yes or no questions. You understand?

651
00:35:13,528 --> 00:35:14,493
Do you understand?!

652
00:35:15,323 --> 00:35:17,812
Have you seen Amelia Delongpre
in the last two weeks?

653
00:35:18,835 --> 00:35:21,121
Did you conspire with her 
to blackmail Kane Software?

654
00:35:21,335 --> 00:35:23,968
He doesn't know. If he falls, 
he's going to break his neck.

655
00:35:24,058 --> 00:35:27,819
Did you conspire with her 
to blackmail Kane Software?

656
00:35:29,137 --> 00:35:31,013
Did you kill Amelia Delongpre?

657
00:35:32,613 --> 00:35:35,438
Wow. Where'd you learn 
that interrogation technique?

658
00:35:35,550 --> 00:35:36,728
Harvard.

659
00:35:36,985 --> 00:35:40,589
That's a pretty convincing hysterical 
routine you got. Where'd you learn that?

660
00:35:40,665 --> 00:35:44,083
Watching cheerleading-tryout results. 
Do you think he did it?

661
00:35:44,319 --> 00:35:46,249
Nah. No one's that good a liar.

662
00:35:46,342 --> 00:35:49,481
Another sweet thing is 
I'm in constant video contact

663
00:35:49,557 --> 00:35:50,720
with Martha Stewart, right?

664
00:35:50,822 --> 00:35:52,872
It's kind of like a 
"Dick Tracy" kind of thing.

665
00:35:52,957 --> 00:35:54,206
What the hell is this, man?

666
00:35:58,209 --> 00:36:00,090
Esta...una...

667
00:36:01,665 --> 00:36:03,241
What is their word for "paper"?

668
00:36:03,454 --> 00:36:04,859
Uh, "papero"?

669
00:36:06,776 --> 00:36:09,279
Okay, I'll translate. 
Just don't tell the ESL teacher

670
00:36:09,335 --> 00:36:10,112
I helped you cheat.

671
00:36:12,198 --> 00:36:13,872
That's an eviction notice.

672
00:36:13,946 --> 00:36:15,369
You bought my grandmother's house?

673
00:36:15,436 --> 00:36:16,066
That's right.

674
00:36:16,169 --> 00:36:18,610
Su casa is mi casa.

675
00:36:18,886 --> 00:36:21,377
But in my defense, 
Weevil, I do need a new one.

676
00:36:21,473 --> 00:36:26,658
You might have heard my former domicile 
was, uh, burned quite unexpectedly.

677
00:36:26,782 --> 00:36:28,630
If you kick my family out --

678
00:36:28,855 --> 00:36:30,197
have it your way -- we'll all live together

679
00:36:30,437 --> 00:36:32,636
in one big, wacky sitcom family.

680
00:36:33,657 --> 00:36:35,745
On second thought, I'm kicking you out.

681
00:36:35,924 --> 00:36:37,154
And on third thought,

682
00:36:37,257 --> 00:36:39,549
I wouldn't live in that roach motel
if you put a gun to my --

683
00:36:39,600 --> 00:36:40,624
hey!

684
00:36:42,066 --> 00:36:43,207
I was enjoying that.

685
00:36:43,319 --> 00:36:45,473
Not as much as I'm going to enjoy this.

686
00:36:45,649 --> 00:36:47,467
Teacher: Hey, hey, hey! Hey, hey, hey!

687
00:36:47,725 --> 00:36:50,089
Break it up! Come on, guys.

688
00:36:50,639 --> 00:36:52,802
School is not the place 
for this kind of thing.

689
00:36:53,029 --> 00:36:55,045
You hear that? 
School is a place of learning.

690
00:36:55,383 --> 00:36:57,439
You might want to think about 
what prison is a place of.

691
00:37:05,885 --> 00:37:09,462
I usually digest a week like this
with a little help from Wallace.

692
00:37:09,553 --> 00:37:13,202
I still do, but now the conversation
is a bit flat and one-sided.

693
00:37:13,548 --> 00:37:17,354
"Dear wallace, me again, 
with the latest news you've been missing.

694
00:37:17,484 --> 00:37:22,429
Keith Mars loses sheriff's race by a nose. 
Logan echolls jailed for" --

695
00:37:30,900 --> 00:37:31,864
Are you Veronica?

696
00:37:31,977 --> 00:37:33,633
Yes.

697
00:37:34,508 --> 00:37:36,520
I saw your post on the Ibiza forum.

698
00:37:36,713 --> 00:37:38,026
Is this the girl you're looking for?

699
00:37:43,010 --> 00:37:47,224
That's her, but actually, 
um... she's been found, but thanks --

700
00:37:47,292 --> 00:37:49,076
tell me she's not still with her boyfriend.

701
00:37:49,181 --> 00:37:50,756
The guy next to her in the picture?

702
00:37:51,489 --> 00:37:51,846
Yeah.

703
00:37:52,065 --> 00:37:56,562
He seems cool, but I've never seen a guy lie 
right into your face and you'd never guess.

704
00:38:02,619 --> 00:38:03,985
Palm Tree Lodge.

705
00:38:04,089 --> 00:38:05,120
Hi, remember me?

706
00:38:05,185 --> 00:38:05,646
The blonde?

707
00:38:05,698 --> 00:38:07,519
Holy crap. You know the cops have just --

708
00:38:07,623 --> 00:38:10,389
I know. I'm guessing you're 
on e-mail right now. What's your address?

709
00:38:10,483 --> 00:38:13,417
Nightman122@aol.Com.

710
00:38:17,525 --> 00:38:20,527
The guy in the white buick, 
the night the redhead was there.

711
00:38:20,592 --> 00:38:21,547
Is that him in the picture?

712
00:38:21,769 --> 00:38:27,106
Yeah, that's him, but he didn't have that 
beard thing and his hair was a lot shorter.

713
00:38:30,796 --> 00:38:35,250
Hi, it's me again. Amelia's boyfriend
did he have a little beard thing right here?

714
00:38:35,367 --> 00:38:36,155
Yeah.

715
00:38:36,343 --> 00:38:37,801
Do you remember his name?

716
00:38:40,411 --> 00:38:41,235
Clarence Wiedman.

717
00:38:41,287 --> 00:38:43,244
The killer -- his name is Carlos Mercado.

718
00:38:43,312 --> 00:38:44,018
Good.

719
00:38:44,373 --> 00:38:46,242
Some of the marked bills 
showed up at caesars palace.

720
00:38:46,330 --> 00:38:48,025
Now we have a name and a place.

721
00:38:48,079 --> 00:38:51,329
All you need, but...
he's a diplomat's son, Clarence.

722
00:38:51,379 --> 00:38:53,338
He'll be extradited to Argentina.

723
00:38:53,385 --> 00:38:54,980
That depends on what happens at the casino.

724
00:38:55,381 --> 00:38:56,667
What are you going to do?

725
00:38:56,794 --> 00:38:58,060
You know the drill, Veronica.

726
00:38:58,460 --> 00:39:00,862
What happens in Vegas stays in Vegas.

727
00:39:03,636 --> 00:39:05,649
So, I did what Abel Koontz asked.

728
00:39:05,875 --> 00:39:09,472
But how do you tell a dying man that 
the daughter he was looking for is gone,

729
00:39:09,637 --> 00:39:13,722
that the millions he sacrificed his own
life to give her only led to her death?

730
00:39:14,895 --> 00:39:15,956
Excuse me, nurse.

731
00:39:16,116 --> 00:39:18,713
Abel Koontz -- how's he doing?

732
00:39:20,820 --> 00:39:22,964
A day or two, if he's lucky.

733
00:39:26,333 --> 00:39:26,846
Thank you.

734
00:39:28,699 --> 00:39:30,835
Answer -- you don't.

735
00:39:32,832 --> 00:39:34,289
She's trying to make it.

736
00:39:34,675 --> 00:39:37,559
They just had an early snow this year, so...

737
00:39:38,559 --> 00:39:40,072
she's just waiting for a helicopter.

738
00:39:41,868 --> 00:39:43,425
But she's happy?

739
00:39:46,198 --> 00:39:46,904
Yeah.

740
00:39:47,617 --> 00:39:51,347
Hoofing the Himalayas isn't exactly 
my idea of a good time, but...

741
00:39:52,916 --> 00:39:54,061
she seemed to love it.

742
00:39:57,865 --> 00:40:01,948
In a family full of well-intentioned lies, 
